Ward {4}
Kosmen, the World Mind&#39;s power and toughness are each equal to the number of artifacts you control.
{U}, {T}: Gain control of target artifact with mana value less than Kosmen&#39;s power for as long as you control Kosmen. If it&#39;s not a creature, you may have it become an artifact creature with power and toughness each equal to its mana value for as long as you control it.

[+1]: Sacrifice an artifact. Search your library for an artifact or creature card with mana value equal to 1 plus the sacrificed artifact’s mana value, put that card onto the battlefield, then shuffle.
[-2]: Until the start of your next turn, counters can&#39;t be removed from permanents you control.
[-5]: You get an emblem with &quot;&quot;Spells you cast cost {1} less for each artifact you control.&quot;&quot;

Ward {6}
{6}:  Until end of turn, each nontoken artifact you control becomes an artifact creature with power and toughness each equal to its mana value and gains hexproof.
{6}, Exile Soul of Namekkos from your graveyard:  Until end of turn, each nontoken artifact you control becomes an artifact creature with power and toughness each equal to its mana value and gains hexproof.
